                    <span>Despite the ever present 1 star reviewer (s), this is one great book by Robert Allen. I don't understand why this guy continues to bash Robert Allen and other successful authors. It does tell us how this person spends his time though doesn't it?<P>In Multiple Streams of Income, Robert Allen reveals strategies and ideas that are right for the times. People who have been downsized, unemployed or even worse, underemployed and/or tired of the rat race, corporate lemmings etc. will find new hope with strategies that really work.<P>I can't help but notice the continual attacks on network marketing. All this tells me is that this basher has probably tried and failed in network marketing and therefore chooses to attack it. Or is incredibly ignorant. Just look at the earnings reports of any of the publicly traded companies or read any of the network marketing trade publications to see just how this great inductry is doing.<P>I have found a company that is only a year and ahalf old and is already doing $40 Million in sales with projections of hitting $1 Billion by 2007. Network marketing is alive and well. There is also a website that can bring you up to speed on the current state of network marketing http://www.myxongo.com/platinumteam<P>But if you don't like network marketing, that's okay. Allen offers 7 other dynamic income streams that don't involve network marketing, can be started with little or no money and offer high return with very little if any risk.<P>Besides network marketing, I have been enjoying a nice income with the Copper Cover Calls technique and 3 other strategies. This is great book and America owes Mr. Allen a debt of gratitude for sharing this powerful information for the rest of us. <P>Thank you Robert!</span>
                  
                    <div class="CustomerReviewSummary">Escaped the rat race, thank you Robert</div>
