                    <span>While I admire the success of people like the reviewer who precedes mine, network marketing never really appealed to me. I tried it once back in the 70's, had a lousy sponsor who didn't teach me beans and the company I was in loaded me and other distributors with soaps, shampoo's and so on.<P>That said, what I like about Robert Allen's book is that he recommends network marketing as a choice but also recommends other ways to create residual income, that are low risk and low cost.<P>I highly recommend this book by Mr. Allen. It's great.</span>
                  
                    <div class="CustomerReviewSummary">Multiple ways of creating income and wealth</div>
                    <div>
                      <span class="ItemCaption">Rating: </span>
                      <span>5</span>
